\begin_layout Subsubsection
Calculation of seasonal bushfire potential 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Bushfire potential can be estimated using weather variables.
 Temperature, relative humidity, wind and precipitation are common variables
 used for this purpose.
 This variables can be combined in mathematical equations.
 This equations reflect vaiable's relationships in producing the conditions
 for bushfires to occur.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This equations are known are bushfire indices.
 The McArthur Forest Fire Danger Index (FFDI) is used in Australia.
 The index is represented as an equation (citation):
